cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a new cryptographic method and model for confidentiality and authentication, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of mathematical tools and pattern finding also suggests the possibility of information theory (cs.IT) being a relevant sub-category. The development of an algorithm and use of block chaining modes of operation indicate the involvement of computer communication (cs.CC) and security and privacy (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of shared key cryptosystems and digital enveloping suggests the involvement of software engineering (cs.SE) as well.
